# Keep repo-root Docker builds small. The Web Client and Browser CI image use
# the repo root as build context so they can consume constraints.txt.
*

!constraints.txt

!.github/
.github/*
!.github/docker/
.github/docker/*
!.github/docker/ijt-browser-ci/**

!OPC_UA_Clients/
OPC_UA_Clients/*
!OPC_UA_Clients/Release2/
OPC_UA_Clients/Release2/*
!OPC_UA_Clients/Release2/IJT_Web_Client/**

# Allow the shared readiness module to be vendored into the Web Client
# Docker test image (see OPC_UA_Clients/Release2/IJT_Web_Client/Dockerfile,
# test stage). tests/python/_live_server_readiness.py imports it at runtime.
!scripts/
scripts/*
!scripts/ijt_live_readiness.py

**/__pycache__/
**/*.py[cod]
**/.venv/
**/.venv_test/
**/.venv_ci/
**/venv/
**/venv_test/
**/node_modules/
**/logs/
**/.state/
**/tmp/
**/test-results/
**/.pytest_cache/
**/.ruff_cache/
**/.mypy_cache/
